This paper is about a technique for regularizing artificial neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper specifically mentions that the technique can be used with fully-connected and convolutional neural networks, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions that the technique can be used with text data, which is a common application in natural language processing (cs.CL).
